Unfortunately, during the second pandemic wave, we have dropped our guard.Relevant government administrators, health officials and citizens seem fatigued. 2020 will stand as a challenging year as 1982 and 2008. Covid-19’s devastation is comparable to that occasioned by the 1982 attempted coup ’de tat and the aftermath of the 2007 post-election civil strife.
Coronavirus caught us unawares. Substantial budgetary resources had to be diverted to deal with the pandemic in response to an overstretched health system.



