The national government employed extra health staff and interns to augment the personnel numbers. Also, counties supplemented their health personnel.
Personal protective equipment, ICU facilities and other oxygen delivery systems were also required as well as an enhanced risk allowance and comprehensive medical cover.
Unfortunately, during the second pandemic wave, we have dropped our guard. Relevant government administrators, health officials and citizens seem fatigued. This must radically change. And we must also prioritise making the Covid-19 vaccine available nationally.



