Covid-19 has disrupted the educational system. Most school-going children and young people have missed school, college or university for almost a year. We have to endeavour to recover the lost time. As learners reopen this month, Covid-19 protocols must be religiously followed.
Covid-19’s economic impact is massive. Loss of jobs — both formal and informal — and businesses has been astronomical. Between April and June 2020, it was estimated that 1.7 million jobs were lost.
In 2020, we witnessed an unprecedented urban-rural migration. Many micro, Small, and Medium Enterprises also collapsed countrywide.
Although the government has a major revenue shortfall challenge, the previous tax holiday should have been retained. Countries abroad such as the US are giving relief to unemployed citizens.



