The question is begged: When will the majority of the Kenyan population, those who want to run clean business and others desirous of a better and prosperous nation, be mainstreamed into the society?
As of September 2020, the national public debt stood at about Sh7.121 trillion, just shy of the Sh9.0 trillion mandated ceiling. Both debt repayment and the recurrent expenditure are almost consuming the entire current revenue raised by KRA. We need to tame appetite for debt to avoid consigning Kenya into economic doldrums.



